vorgelegt werden musste. Darüber hinaus wird ein Drucktext mit Variantenapparat sowie ein Kommentar geboten. Eingeleitet wird der Band durch eine Darstellung der Entstehungs- und Druckgeschichte.  aIn The Green Cockatoo, a one-act play from 1898, Arthur Schnitzler thematizes the indistinguishability of fiction and reality. The historical-critical edition reconstructs the history of the play and its publication, presents archival materials, and provides a print text and commentary. Moreover, it documents the censorship of the premiere at the Burgtheater in Vienna in 1899.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by FWF  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aSchnitzler, Arthur. 4aWiener Moderne. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aSchnitzler, Arthur.  aWiener Moderne.1 aLindner, Anna, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt2 aFWFefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU0 cprintz978311067626640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110677058zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110677058zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110677058/original  a978-3-11-075070-6 DG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020  aZDB-23-GOA